<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Nabeshima</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-15"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 40.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 12th instant, and to say in reply that the
                            complaints made by you of the quarantine regulations of Colorado and San
                            Francisco are receiving the careful consideration of the Department, the
                            result of which will be communicated to you as soon as a conclusion is
                            reached.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>